# Swiss Wayfinding Design System

## Design Influences
1. **German Road Signage** (Bundesautobahn) - Clear hierarchy, functional color
2. **Rudy Bauer Design Studio** - Cologne Bonn Airport (CGN) wayfinding
3. **Swiss International Typographic Style** - Grid, Helvetica, density

## Core Principles

| Principle | Implementation |
|-----------|----------------|
| Clarity | Hierarchy through scale/weight, not decoration |
| Density | Maximum useful information per viewport |
| Systematic | Consistent patterns, universally applied |
| Functional Color | Color = meaning, never decorative |
| Wayfinding | User always knows location and navigation |

## Typography

```scss
// Font stacks
--font-primary: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, 'Liberation Sans', sans-serif;
--font-mono: 'SF Mono', Consolas, 'Liberation Mono', monospace;

// Scale (base 14px, ratio 1.25)
--text-xs: 0.64rem;    // 9px - timestamps, meta
--text-sm: 0.8rem;     // 11px - captions, secondary
--text-base: 1rem;     // 14px - body text
--text-md: 1.25rem;    // 17.5px - card titles
--text-lg: 1.563rem;   // 22px - section headers
--text-xl: 1.953rem;   // 27px - page titles
--text-2xl: 2.441rem;  // 34px - hero text
```

### Typography Rules
- **ALL CAPS**: Navigation, status labels, section headers
- **Sentence case**: Body text, descriptions
- **Tabular numerals**: All notation (i5, s23, 2609.5.56)
- **Letter-spacing**: +0.02em for all-caps, 0 for body
- **No italics** except `<cite>` elements
- **Weights**: 400 body, 500 headings, 700 emphasis

